@startuml optic_batching_n_plus_one

!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ncosta-ic/catppuccin-macchiato-plantuml-theme/main/theme.puml

title N+1 vs Batched: same shape, two strategies

participant "Caller" as C
participant "Traversal\nover N ids" as T
participant "Backend" as B

== Without batching (N+1) ==
C -> T : modifyF(loadOne, ids)
loop N times (one per focus)
    T -> B : loadOne(id)
    B --> T : entity
end
T --> C : List<entity>

== With FetchApplicative (one round) ==
C -> T : modifyF(Fetch.fetch, ids,\n   FetchApplicative)
note right of T
  ap() merges pending
  request sets, so foci
  share a single round
end note
T -> B : batchResolver({id_1, ..., id_N})
B --> T : Map<id, entity>
T --> C : List<entity>

@enduml
